    "content": "<p>For the dual-wheel carrying assembly shown in the figure, P is the load on each wheel, a is the radius of the contact area of the wheel, s is the spacing between the wheels, and d is the clear distance between the wheels. Assuming that the ground is an elastic, homogenous, and isotropic half space, the ratio of Equivalent Single Wheel Load (ESWL) at depth z = d/2 to the ESWL at depth z = 2s is __________. (round off to one decimal place)</p>\n<p>(Consider the influence angle to be 45$$^\\circ$$ for the linear dispersion of stress with depth)</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1m1i38l5q/9782267e-2c89-4e62-a174-b1d656ac4126/64df53e0-7b5c-11ef-9784-6f5290825d2e/file-jaoe38c1m1i38l5r.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1m1i38l5q/9782267e-2c89-4e62-a174-b1d656ac4126/64df53e0-7b5c-11ef-9784-6f5290825d2e/file-jaoe38c1m1i38l5r.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"GATE CE 2022 Set 1 Transportation Engineering - Pavement Design Question 3 English\"></p>",
    "options": [],
